# Next.js Routing Structure

All new pages should be created under the `(protected)` route group unless explicitly specified otherwise.

## Route Group Structure

- **Protected Routes**: [src/app/(protected)/](mdc:src/app/(protected)/) - Default location for all new pages
- **Landing Pages**: [src/app/(landing)/](mdc:src/app/(landing)/) - Only for public landing pages
- **Auth Routes**: [src/app/auth/](mdc:src/app/auth/) - Authentication-related pages only

## Default Behavior

When creating new pages or routes:
1. Always place them under `src/app/(protected)/` unless told otherwise
2. Use the existing layout structure from [src/app/(protected)/layout.tsx](mdc:src/app/(protected)/layout.tsx)
3. Follow the established pattern of creating `page.tsx` files in appropriately named directories

## Examples

- New dashboard feature: `src/app/(protected)/dashboard/feature/page.tsx`
- Backend testing page: `src/app/(protected)/backend/test/page.tsx`
- User settings: `src/app/(protected)/settings/page.tsx`

Only create pages outside the `(protected)` group when explicitly requested for public access or authentication flows.
